Hello,

Iâ€™m updating a custom landing page template and when updating the landing page template settings with the new template, the Form Headline module is being omitted.

Any insights on why this is happening? The inclusion of column/rows in the structure?

Previous Template
```{% dnd_section max_width=1250, padding={"top": "80px", "bottom": "80px", "left": "5%", "right": "5%"},  vertical_alignment="MIDDLE" %}
  {% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/rich_text', 
    width=7, offset=0,
    label="Rich Text" %}
      {% module_attribute "html"%}
      <div class="get__hero-text">
        CONTENT HERE
        </div>
      </div>
      {% end_module_attribute %}
  {% end_dnd_module %}
  {% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/form.module' width=5, offset=7,%}
  {% end_dnd_module %}
{% end_dnd_section %}```
New Template
```{% dnd_section max_width=1250, padding={"top": "80px", "bottom": "80px", "left": "5%", "right": "5%"},  vertical_alignment="MIDDLE" %}
  {% dnd_column, width=7, offset=0, %}
    {% dnd_row %}
      {% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/rich_text', 
        label="Rich Text" %}
          {% module_attribute "html"%}
          <div class="get__hero-text">
            CONTENT HERE
            </div>
          </div>
          {% end_module_attribute %}
      {% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_row %}
  {% end_dnd_column %}
  {% dnd_column, width=5, offset=7, class="get-started-form" %}
    {% dnd_row %}
      {% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/rich_text', label="Form Headline" %}
        {% module_attribute "html"%}
          <h2>Request a Quote</h2> 
        {% end_module_attribute %}
      {% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_row %}
    {% dnd_row %}
      {% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/form.module'%}
      {% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_row %}
  {% end_dnd_column %}
{% end_dnd_section %}```
